President Barack Obama has declared May 2013 as National Mental Health Awareness Month. The proclamation highlights the millions of Americans living with mental health problems and the need to address these issues. The president emphasizes the importance of starting a conversation and seeking help for mental health conditions, as well as the need to combat shame and stigma. The Affordable Care Act is mentioned as a way to expand mental health and substance use disorder benefits for millions of Americans. The president also mentions the BRAIN Initiative, which aims to invest in research for new treatments for mental illness. The proclamation concludes by calling upon citizens, government agencies, organizations, healthcare providers, and research institutions to raise awareness and continue helping Americans with mental health issues.